investigation.title: Rodent Research-3-CASIS: Mouse adrenal gland transcriptomic, proteomic, and epigenomic data
investigation.description: The Rodent Research-3 (RR-3) mission was sponsored by the pharmaceutical company Eli Lilly and Co. and the Center for the Advancement of Science in Space to study the effectiveness of a potential countermeasure for the loss of muscle and bone mass that occurs during spaceflight.

project.funding: This investigation was funded by the ISS National Lab, the NASA Space Biology Program Office, Space Life and Physical Sciences Research and Applications Division and additional funding from the International Space Station Research Integration Office to the Space Biology GeneLab Project
